cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MA 

The paper discusses the network-layer modeling and configuration of programmable wireless environments, which involves the design and optimization of wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions eavesdropping and security, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a graph-based model, which could suggest it belongs to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the model using simulation tools, which could place it in cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
